In July 2017 The Irish Times reported new figures on breastfeeding rates. These were provided by the HSE to Fianna Fail spokesperson Billy Kelleher. They provided the rates of mothers breastfeeding at the first visit of the Public Health Nurse (PHN) which is usually within days of the birth and at the three month visit. Rates vary considerably, from 84% in Dublin South East to 40% in South Tipperary at the time of the first visit. By the visit at three months the rates range from 66% in Dublin South East fo 20% in Donegal.
